HEADWORD: Anorthoscope
<hw>A*nor"tho*scope</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'an</grk> priv. + <grk>'orqo`s</grk> straight +
<ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An optical toy for
producing amusing figures or pictures by means of two revolving disks,
on one of which distorted figures are painted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

